020package org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.internal;
021
022import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.INTERNAL;
023import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.STABLE;
024import static org.tquadrat.foundation.lang.Objects.requireNonNullArgument;
025
026import javax.lang.model.element.TypeParameterElement;
027import javax.lang.model.type.ArrayType;
028import java.io.UncheckedIOException;
029import java.lang.reflect.GenericArrayType;
030import java.lang.reflect.Type;
031import java.util.ArrayList;
032import java.util.List;
033import java.util.Map;
034
035import org.apiguardian.api.API;
036import org.tquadrat.foundation.annotation.ClassVersion;
037import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.AnnotationSpec;
038import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.ArrayTypeName;
039import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.TypeName;
040import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.TypeVariableName;
041
042/**
043 *  The implementation of
044 *  {@link TypeNameImpl}
045 *  for array types.
046 *
047 *  @author Square,Inc.
048 *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
049 *  @version $Id: ArrayTypeNameImpl.java 1085 2024-01-05 16:23:28Z tquadrat $
050 *  @since 0.0.5
051 *
052 *  @UMLGraph.link
053 */
054@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: ArrayTypeNameImpl.java 1085 2024-01-05 16:23:28Z tquadrat $" )
055@API( status = INTERNAL, since = "0.0.5" )
056public final class ArrayTypeNameImpl extends TypeNameImpl implements ArrayTypeName
057{
058        /*------------*\
059    ====** Attributes **=======================================================
060        \*------------*/
061    /**
062     *  The array component type.
063     */
064    @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
065    private final TypeNameImpl m_ComponentType;
066
067        /*--------------*\
068    ====** Constructors **=====================================================
069        \*--------------*/
070    /**
071     *  Creates a new {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} instance.
072     *
073     *  @param  componentType   The type of the array components.
074     */
075    @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
076    public ArrayTypeNameImpl( final TypeNameImpl componentType ) { this( componentType, new ArrayList<>() ); }
077
078    /**
079     *  Creates a new {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} instance.
080     *
081     *  @param  componentType   The type of the array components.
082     *  @param  annotations The annotations for this array type name.
083     */
084    @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
085    public ArrayTypeNameImpl( final TypeNameImpl componentType, final List<AnnotationSpecImpl> annotations )
086    {
087        super( annotations );
088        m_ComponentType = requireNonNullArgument( componentType, "componentType" );
089    }   //  ArrayTypeNameImpl()
090
091        /*---------*\
092    ====** Methods **==========================================================
093        \*---------*/
094    /**
095     *  {@inheritDoc}
096     */
097    @Override
098    public final ArrayTypeNameImpl annotated( final List<AnnotationSpec> annotations )
099    {
100        return new ArrayTypeNameImpl( getComponentType(), concatAnnotations( annotations ) );
101    }   //  annotated()
102
103    /**
104     *  {@inheritDoc}
105     */
106    @Override
107    public final TypeName componentType() { return getComponentType(); }
108
109    /**
110     *  {@inheritDoc}
111     */
112    @SuppressWarnings( {"PublicMethodNotExposedInInterface", "UseOfConcreteClass"} )
113    @Override
114    public final CodeWriter emit( final CodeWriter out ) throws UncheckedIOException { return emit( out, false ); }
115
116    /**
117     *  Emits this type name instance to the given
118     *  {@link CodeWriter}.
119     *
120     *  @param  out The code writer.
121     *  @param  varargs {@code true} if the array should be emitted as varargs
122     *      (obviously this affects only arrays used in method signatures),
123     *      {@code false} for the usual representation.
124     *  @return The code writer.
125     *  @throws UncheckedIOException Something went wrong when writing to the
126     *      output target.
127     */
128    @SuppressWarnings( {"PublicMethodNotExposedInInterface", "UseOfConcreteClass"} )
129    public final CodeWriter emit( final CodeWriter out, final boolean varargs ) throws UncheckedIOException
130    {
131        final var retValue = requireNonNullArgument( out, "out" );
132        emitLeafType( retValue );
133        emitBrackets( retValue, varargs );
134
135        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
136        return retValue;
137    }   //  emit()
138
139    /**
140     *  Emits the annotations and the brackets for the array.
141     *
142     *  @param  out The code writer.
143     *  @param  varargs {@code true} if the array should be emitted as varargs
144     *      (obviously this affects only arrays used in method signatures),
145     *      {@code false} for the usual representation.
146     *  @return The code writer.
147     *  @throws UncheckedIOException Something went wrong when writing to the
148     *      output target.
149     */
150    @SuppressWarnings( {"UnusedReturnValue", "UseOfConcreteClass"} )
151    private final CodeWriter emitBrackets( final CodeWriter out, final boolean varargs ) throws UncheckedIOException
152    {
153        final var retValue = requireNonNullArgument( out, "out" );
154        if( isAnnotated() )
155        {
156            retValue.emit( " " );
157            emitAnnotations( retValue );
158        }
159
160        final var arrayInArray = asArray( getComponentType() );
161        if( arrayInArray.isPresent() )
162        {
163            retValue.emit( "[]" );
164            arrayInArray.get().emitBrackets( retValue, varargs );
165        }
166        else
167        {
168            //---* Last bracket *----------------------------------------------
169            retValue.emit( varargs ? "..." : "[]" );
170        }
171
172        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
173        return retValue;
174    }   //  emitBrackets()
175
176    /**
177     *  Emits the array's component type.
178     *
179     *  @param  out The code writer.
180     *  @return The code writer.
181     *  @throws UncheckedIOException Something went wrong when writing to the
182     *      output target.
183     */
184    @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
185    private final CodeWriter emitLeafType( final CodeWriter out ) throws UncheckedIOException
186    {
187        final var arrayInArray = asArray( getComponentType() );
188        final var retValue = arrayInArray.isPresent()
189            ? arrayInArray.get().emitLeafType( out )
190            : getComponentType().emit( out );
191
192        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
193        return retValue;
194    }   //  emitLeafType()
195
196    /**
197     *  Returns an instance of {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} for an array type
198     *  that is equivalent to {@code mirror}.
199     *
200     *  @param  mirror  The mirror for the array.
201     *  @param  typeVariables   The type variables.
202     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
203     */
204    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
205    public static final ArrayTypeNameImpl from( final ArrayType mirror, final Map<TypeParameterElement,TypeVariableNameImpl> typeVariables )
206    {
207        final var retValue = new ArrayTypeNameImpl( TypeNameImpl.from( requireNonNullArgument( mirror, "mirror" ).getComponentType(), typeVariables ) );
208
209        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
210        return retValue;
211    }   //  from()
212
213    /**
214     *  Returns an instance of {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} for an array type that
215     *  is equivalent to {@code type}.
216     *
217     *  @param  type    The array type.
218     *  @param  typeVariables   The type variables.
219     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
220     */
221    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
222    public static final ArrayTypeNameImpl from( final GenericArrayType type, final Map<Type,TypeVariableName> typeVariables )
223    {
224        final var retValue = of( TypeNameImpl.from( requireNonNullArgument( type, "type" ).getGenericComponentType(), typeVariables ) );
225
226        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
227        return retValue;
228    }   //  from()
229
230    /**
231     *  Returns the array component type.
232     *
233     * @return The array component type.
234     */
235    @SuppressWarnings( {"PublicMethodNotExposedInInterface"} )
236    public final TypeNameImpl getComponentType() { return m_ComponentType; }
237
238    /**
239     *  Returns an array type whose elements are all instances of the given
240     *  component type.
241     *
242     *  @param  componentType   The component type.
243     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
244     */
245    public static ArrayTypeNameImpl of( final Type componentType )
246    {
247        return of( TypeNameImpl.from( requireNonNullArgument( componentType, "componentType" ) ) );
248    }   //  of()
249
250    /**
251     *  Returns an array type whose elements are all instances of the given
252     *  component type.
253     *
254     *  @param  componentType   The component type.
255     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
256     */
257    public static final ArrayTypeNameImpl of( final TypeName componentType )
258    {
259        return new ArrayTypeNameImpl( (TypeNameImpl) componentType );
260    }   //  of()
261
262    /**
263     *  {@inheritDoc}
264     */
265    @Override
266    public final ArrayTypeNameImpl withoutAnnotations() { return new ArrayTypeNameImpl( getComponentType() ); }
267}
268//  class ArrayTypeNameImpl
